description.narrative: Output 5.1: The capacity of relevant actors to manage and provide social welfare services and birth registration services improved by 2019 (UNDAF. OUTPUT 3.3.1, 3.3.2) UNICEF GAP 2.0 Mainstreaming Priorities- goal 5: Gender equitable socialization care and support for girls and boys., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Protection Systems, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 5: By 2019, the most vulnerable children, adolescents, and young people benefit from quality essential social services and social safety nets and live in a safe and protective environment

description.narrative: Enhanced capacity of 455 statutory workers (67 social workers, 388 health workers) on child protection (CP) helped improve delivery of social welfare, birth registration (BR) and case management services to children. The strengthened capacity of health workers contributed to the registration and certification of at least 112,249 children under 13, of which 41,626 children (20,131 boys, 21,495 girls), or 22.7%, were children under age 5; and 32,800 children (17,167 boys, 15,633 girls), or 35.2%, were children under age 1. Another 1,426 children (708 boys, 718 girls) who experienced violence were reached by health, social work or justice services. | Status:Met | As-of Date:16/01/2020
